'''Larry A. Lemak, M.D.''', FAAOS, FCRSC, born 1943 in [[Pittsburgh]], [[Pennsylvania]] is an [[orthopedic]] [[surgeon]] who practices at the '''Lemak Sports Medicine & Orthopedics ''' in [[Birmingham, Alabama|Birmingham]], [[Alabama]], located at Trinity Medical Center (Birmingham). Dr. Lemak is one of the most renowned sports medicine and orthopedic surgeon in his profession for arthroscopy and reconstruction of the knee, shoulder, hip and elbow.<ref>{{cite web|title=SMART's Dr. Larry Lemak is name Sports Medicine Person of the Year|url=http://hscweb3.hsc.usf.edu/health/now/?p=119}}</ref> 

In 1986, Lemak and his partner [[James Andrews (physician)|James Andrews, M.D]]., founded the '''Alabama Sports Medicine and Orthopedic Center (ASMOC)''' as well as the '''[[American Sports Medicine Institute]] (ASMI)''' in Birmingham. Dr. Lemak has played an integral role in sports medicine and arthroscopy research as a founder and member of the board of directors for the American Sports Medicine Institute (ASMI). 

In 2001 Lemak founded the [[National Center for Sports Safety]], a non-profit organization dedicated to promoting the importance of injury prevention and safety in youth sports.<ref>{{cite web|last=ARON|first=JAIME|title=Pop Warner: Doctor's OK Needed for Concussed Kids|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Sports/wireStory?id=12182118#.TrlQDrL6NnA|publisher=Associated Press}}</ref> 

On October 8, 2009 the [[United Football League (2009â€“)|United Football League]] announced that Dr. Lemak would serve as Chief Medical Officer to the League.<ref>{{cite web|title=United Football League Announces Dr. Lawrence Lemak As Chief Medical Officer|url=http://www.oursportscentral.com/services/releases/?id=3914495}}</ref> 

Dr. Lemak is a member and Fellow of the [[American Academy of Orthopaedic Surgeons|American Academy of Orthopedic Surgeons]] (FAAOS) and member of and the [[American Orthopaedic Society for Sports Medicine]]. Dr. Lemak serves as Medical Director for [[Major League Soccer]], the [[Professional Golfers Association|PGA]] and the [[LPGA]] and formerly for [[NFL Europe]]. In addition, he serves as team physician for [[Auburn University]], [[Samford University]], [[Birmingham-Southern College]] and as the Sports Commissioner for the State of [[Alabama]]. 

Dr. Lemak is a clinical assistant professor at the [[University of Virginia]] and the [[University of Alabama at Birmingham]]. 

Dr. Lemak is a Board Certified surgeon, with a Medical degree from the [[University of Alabama]] and an Orthopaedic Residency completed at the [[University of Pittsburgh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Profile|url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=7701194&privcapId=842063&previousCapId=842063&previousTitle=Source%20Medical%20Solutions,%20Inc.|publisher=Bloombergs Businessweek}}</ref>

